Malicious software discovered in app development kits for Android and iOS by Kaspersky Labs, capable of scanning for crypto wallet recovery phrases.
news.summary: According to Kaspersky Labs, a recently discovered software development kit used for creating apps on Google and Apple phones has been found to contain malware. This malicious software is capable of scanning images to locate crypto wallet recovery phrases. This poses a significant security threat to users as it could potentially lead to the theft of cryptocurrency funds. It is advised to exercise caution when using apps developed with this particular kit to prevent any potential loss.

news.headline: California Apartment Association and Corporate Landlord under investigation for shady campaign contributions related to Prop 33 and Prop 34 in California. Housing Is A Human Right group reports.
news.summary: An investigation has been launched into the California Apartment Association and a corporate landlord in Los Angeles for allegedly making dubious campaign contributions. The contributions were intended to defeat Proposition 33 and pass Proposition 34. The investigation into the matter was announced by HHR. The specific amounts of the contributions and further details of the investigation have not been disclosed.

news.headline: Canaccord Genuity Group Inc. reported Q3 revenue of $451M; wealth management revenue increased by 19.7% to $233M.
news.summary: Canaccord Genuity Group Inc. reported a third quarter dividend of $0.085 per common share and financial results for the quarter ending December 31, 2024. The third quarter revenue increased by 15.9% to $451 million, with global wealth management revenue up 19.7% at $233.4 million, and global capital markets revenue up 11% to $210.7 million. Net income before taxes for the quarter was $39.8 million, a decrease of 11% year-over-year. Total client assets in global wealth management were $115.0 billion, a 15.9% increase from the previous year. Canaccord Genuity Capital Markets had revenue of $210.7 million for the quarter, a year-over-year increase of 11%. The company also announced strategic collaborations and business acquisitions.

news.headline: Constellation Software & Topicus.com announce agreement for Yukon subsidiary to acquire 12.3M treasury shares for PLN 85 per share.
news.summary: Constellation Software Inc. and Topicus.com Inc. have disclosed that Topicus’ subsidiary, Yukon Niebieski Kapital B.V., will be acquiring 12,318,863 treasury shares from Asseco Poland S.A. and the Adam Góral Family Foundation. This amounts to 14.84% of the Company’s shares and will be bought at PLN 85 per share under the Treasury Shares Purchase Agreement. The execution of this agreement is contingent upon securing necessary regulatory and antitrust clearances.

news.summary: In a recent update, it has been reported that the unemployment rate in the country has reached its lowest point in over a decade, standing at 3.5%. This figure represents a significant drop from the previous year's rate of 4.2%. The decrease in unemployment has been attributed to strong economic growth and increased job opportunities in various sectors. Additionally, the report highlighted that the number of new jobs created in the last quarter alone exceeded 300,000, signaling a positive trend in the labor market. Experts believe that sustained efforts to boost employment and stimulate the economy have contributed to this favorable outcome. It is anticipated that the government will continue to prioritize policies aimed at further reducing unemployment and supporting job growth in the coming months.

news.headline: Callan JMB prices $5.12M IPO with 1,280,000 shares at $4.00 per share, granting underwriters option for 192,000 more shares.
news.summary: Callan JMB Inc., a logistics company serving the healthcare and emergency management sectors, has announced the pricing of its initial public offering on Feb. 04, 2025. The offering includes 1,280,000 shares of Common Stock at $4.00 per Share, generating about $5,120,000 in gross proceeds for the Company. This amount is before deductions for underwriting discounts, commissions, and estimated offering expenses. Additionally, the underwriters have an option to purchase up to 192,000 additional shares of Common Stock at the same price within 45 days, minus discounts and commissions.
